<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26267i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26267i">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26267i"> 267(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">A</font> despina</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Institutions of the Private Law. Domestic relations]</font>&mdash;The husband was priest in his family, but wife and children alike assisted in its prayers, and took part in the sacrifices to its lares and penates <font color="green">[household gods]</font>. As the Greek called his wife the house-mistress, <mark>&delta;&epsilon;&pi;&omicron;&iota;&nu;&alpha;</mark>, so did the Roman speak of his as <i>materfamilias</i>, the house-mother <font color="green">[the woman of the house]</font>. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 530</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
